<p>San Francisco residents have access to multiple solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, through 2032. California offers additional state-level incentives through the California Solar Initiative and Self-Generation Incentive Program, which can provide cash rebates for battery storage systems. PG&E participates in California's Net Energy Metering (NEM) program, allowing solar customers to receive credits for excess electricity sent back to the grid at retail rates. The city of San Francisco also expedites solar permits and has streamlined its inspection processes, reducing soft costs associated with installation. Property tax exemptions ensure that adding solar panels won't increase your property tax assessment, while the increased home value from solar installation remains tax-free.</p>

